		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1217594">
                  
                  for those of you opposed to most of my tweaks and suggestions, you have to remember that the biggest complaint people seem to have about sorc is how simple they are to play in a group due to spamming cv 1,2,3,4.<br />
<br />
I'm expecting a nerf to CV sooner or later, and the only way to cushion that nerf is to boost up taqs, char, and falling star.<br />
<br />
This will also have the adverse affect of giving viable choices to use for dps while grouping.  Char with additional ticks will make weaving it in with other spells more possible, adding an additional level of complexity if one so desires.<br />
<br />
Taq's is only disadvantage if we remove CV from our lineup is its cast time.  If CV stays the way it is for good, it will need a large boost in damage as well.<br />
<br />
Falling star needs improving.  Easiest way is to remove the root chance, which may be detracting from its damage capability.  I personally feel falling star should be our biggest single target damage nuke.  I know there have been other discussions and posts about making this our big nuke, and for the most part I agree with that view.<br />
<br />
ER needs scaling tweaks<br />
When you first get ER, you can kill 2 dots in 3-4 casts.  Over time it slowly looses that ability, at lvl 50 unless you get lucky with a mimic crit on ER, you aren't going to kill a 2 dot in 3-4 casts.  I understand now why people complained about this ability, because for some, it was a playstyle to them to plop on force barrier and ER 3-4 2 dots dead.  Unfortunately this is only viable in the lower lvls.<br />
Secondly when you compare ER to fireball in terms of energy costs, and total damage, you can see how underpowered ER truely is.  Fireball deals approximately the same total damage as ER, costs less power and is usable from range and doesnt cost endurance.<br />
IF the end cost on ER was removed I dont think anyone would complain about it, however since we know it will stay the energy cost needs a severe reduction, it should cost much less than fireball and deal more damage because of the risk associated with ae'ing mobs within mele range.<br />
<br />
Icequake's scaling is just fubar.  How can you introduce an AE snare and never upgrade it's duration from the first ability to the last.  This makes everyone use the first version because lets face it, the only reason to use it is to snare, not to deal damage, and since the durations dont increase its more power efficient to use the first version that costs much less energy to cast.  Thus allowing more snare casts and longer ae kites.  If the power costs are not adjusted dramatically the snare durations must be rescaled.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
