		<div id="post_message_1217951">
                  
                  I don’t know how raid is going to turn out. I could be death all the time with Chromatic Barrier up or it could be a real live saver. I think you will be right with the buffs from the other classes but I will final know only when raid is in. I will wait and see.<br />
<br />
You use CB in solo against caster mob? Bow using mob I’m dead anyway and melee mob should not reach me because I’m kiting. I did not meet a lot of caster mob so far but I try to avoid soloing because I like the interaction of people in groups. In groups I usually do more damage to myself then the mob is doing with AE to me. If the AE is really serious I try to counter it with the reflection ward. I’ve seen rarely mob with serious AEs, overall encounter in VG are in my opinion to easy and I hope this will change with raids.<br />
<br />
25% root is fluff. I don’t care so much about the graphical effects if I need to turn it of because of bad performance. I think VG has a long way to go before improved graphic effects will not be over shaded by bad performance.<br />
<br />
You need to see the improved crit chance for taq in relation to the max crit chance you can reach fully buffed and with max gear.<br />
Two percent more crits is nothing if you go from 10% crit to 12% crit but it gets serious if it moves your chance from 96% to 98% (it halves the non crit casts) and it gets stupid if it increases the chance from 100% to 102%. I don’t know where we are today, my equipment is not so well but I’ve seen people saying lots of the casts are already crits. Increasing crit chance has a scaling issue. You will reach a limit sometimes. If I would need to design this stuff I would be very careful with crits.<br />
<br />
I totally agree with your tool tip suggestion.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
