A lot of questions <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
1. I count them as: 1x Reflect for each spell type from chromatic halo, 1x Mirror ward, 1x Dispersion Ward and 1x Chromatic Halo (i'm counting it only once here, cause i consider recasting it as soon as one of its bubbles is gone)<br />
<br />
2. The wards are &quot;working as intended&quot; imho in pve: per spell casted on you, you'll loose one ward (tho i've experienced some &quot;normal&quot; attacks from mobs seem to be considered as spells, i.e. you disperse one real spell casted on you -&gt; 1. message like &quot;your mirror ward has reflected XY's Spell&quot; and at the same time you'll get a 2nd message like &quot;your dispersion ward has dispersed XY's attack&quot;)<br />
<br />
3. My experiences with the wards are good when it comes to grouping: as soon as everyone is there, i cast the two barriers and chromatic halo with a precedent amplify effectivity. Once i get the mobs turning to me, this gives the tank a few seconds to regain aggro, the healer to switch to me and me some time to fully burn the mob or deaggro <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /> If you have an eye on your aggro you should be able to recast all the wards again after the fight.<br />
On the other hand, all the wards are useless while soloing, cause if you're fighting a caster mob, its either a 2/3dot which you should be able to burn anyway or a 4dot+ which takes too long to kill to keep your wards up during the fight.
                  
