<br />
Actually it was illusive i wanted to quote but nevermind.<br />
I would like to do &quot;more dmg&quot; on short encounters.<br />
Because in a &quot;good group&quot; stuff just dies too fast.<br />
It has been that way since lvl25 in Trengal...<br />
Of course it would be foolish to ask for something that would reliably put me above a rogue.<br />
<br />
But what are our options ?<br />
1) Under 10 Seconds : CV<br />
2) From 10 to 20 Seconds : CV<br />
3) From 20 to 28 Seconds : CV<br />
<br />
Why Because CV is just better than our other spells.<br />
You could make &quot;other spells&quot; compete with CV dps wise.<br />
But for that you would need 20% worn spell haste.<br />
Needless to say, you will be gimping yourself hardcore if you go that way.<br />
<br />
And even if you accept to gimp yourself with 20% worn spell haste.<br />
You will still be using TWO times more mana than with CV.<br />
<br />
<br />
So what do i want ?<br />
I want &quot;fast brutal expensive&quot; spells, that can put me near a rogue.<br />
But at the price of mediocre efficiency.  <br />
<br />
Taqmir is kinda of a good example.<br />
It does more dmg than CV, it costs more mana than CV.<br />
But for it to work, you need a very specific gear set (Haste/Critic).<br />
<br />
And one spell that will put me &quot;above&quot; the rogue, at the price of horrible efficiency.
                  
		</div>
